'''heart attack''' 

# {{pathology}} Acute [[myocardial infarction]], that is the sudden occurrence of [[coronary thrombosis]] which obstructs the blood supply to the heart, resulting in [[necrosis]] of heart muscle.  It is characterised by sudden severe chest pain, often radiating  to the shoulder, arm, or jaw, shortness of breath, [[nausea]], loss of consciousness, and sometimes resulting in death.